			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerTitleCompanyLabel">Senior Analyst, Media & Entertainment Strategies, Yankee Group</span></td>
		        </tr>
		        <tr>
			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerBioLabel">Michael Goodman is responsible for broadband and mobile entertainment research. This includes gaming (console, PC, online, handheld and mobile) online music and video services. His expertise spans the entertainment value chain, including consumer adoption, retail strategies, content strategies, competitor analysis and partner selection. Prior to joining Yankee Group, he was a marketing representative for Nielsen Media Research, where he was responsible for the design, management, analysis and marketing of custom research projects. In addition to television audience research, topics covered included penetration and usage of new technologies in the home, consumer satisfaction, market profiles and concept testing. Goodman's research is frequently referenced in industry publications, such as The New York Times, The Wall Street Journal and BusinessWeek. In addition, he has spoken at numerous tradeshows, including E3, CES and NAB.</span></td>
